<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-17T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-17T13:00:00-05:00" n="65" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.00/664: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-17T19:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">August 17,
                                        1920—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 18—6:33
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1567. Took up question of communication with Monrovia as directed in your
                            1376, August 16, 4 p.m., with M. de Peretti<note n="17" xml:id="d65fn17">E. M. J. de Peretti, Director of Political and Commercial Affairs,
                                French Foreign Office.</note> this afternoon. He promised to
                            investigate and accord every facility. He also agreed to instruct French
                            representative in sense desired.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>